==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tilde
<hw>Til"de</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., fr. L.
<ets>titulus</ets> a superscription, title, token, sign. See
<er>Title</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>The accentual mark placed over
<it>n</it>, and sometimes over <it>l</it>, in Spanish words [thus,
<it>⟦ntil⟧</it>], indicating that, in pronunciation, the sound of the
following vowel is to be preceded by that of the initial, or
consonantal, <it>y</it>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tile</ent>⟦br⟧
